<h2>What you'll learn about your sleep in the first weeks</h2>
<img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1576566588028-4147f3842f27?w=800&q=80" alt="Smart ring technology" style="width:100%;border-radius:10px;aspect-ratio:16/9;object-fit:cover;margin-bottom:20px;" loading="lazy"/>
<p>The first week is calibration. The ring learns your personal baseline. From the second week you start seeing concrete patterns: alcohol reduces your deep sleep by 20-40%, training after 8pm delays sleep onset, and coffee after 2pm reduces REM sleep.</p>
<p>The most valuable thing isn't the data itself, but the trends over weeks. You can see exactly how your habits affect your recovery with real numbers.</p>
<h2>Is it worth it if I don't have sleep problems?</h2>
<p>Yes, especially if you exercise. Knowing when your body is truly recovered lets you train smarter, not harder. Many amateur athletes train with accumulated fatigue without knowing it, and a ring makes that visible.</p>
<h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
<div class="faq-item"><p class="faq-item__q">Is it uncomfortable to sleep with a ring on your finger?</p><p class="faq-item__a">Most users forget they're wearing it after 2-3 nights. It's much more comfortable than a smartwatch. Current models weigh between 2 and 4 grams.</p></div>
<div class="faq-item"><p class="faq-item__q">Can it detect insomnia or sleep apnea?</p><p class="faq-item__a">The Oura Ring can detect patterns consistent with sleep disruptions and oxygen fluctuations that might indicate apnea, but it's not a medical device. If you suspect apnea, see a doctor.</p></div>
<div class="faq-item"><p class="faq-item__q">Do you have to charge it every night?</p><p class="faq-item__a">No. Battery lasts 6-8 days depending on the model. The typical approach is to charge it during your shower or while having breakfast once a week.</p></div>
<div class="faq-item"><p class="faq-item__q">Does it work the same in all sleeping positions?</p><p class="faq-item__a">Yes. Sensors work regardless of whether you sleep on your back, side or stomach. Position doesn't affect measurement accuracy.</p></div>
<div class="faq-item"><p class="faq-item__q">Can it be worn on the pinky?</p><p class="faq-item__a">You can but it's not recommended. For best accuracy, manufacturers recommend the index, middle or ring finger of the non-dominant hand.</p></div>
<div class="faq-item"><p class="faq-item__q">Which is best for women who want cycle tracking?</p><p class="faq-item__a">The Oura Ring 4 has the most advanced menstrual cycle algorithm on the market, using body temperature to predict phases up to 3 days in advance. Samsung Galaxy Ring also includes this function.</p></div>
</div>
